column1: # SuperDARN MSTID Index
# Generated by Nathaniel Frissell
# MongoDB_database: mstid_2016
# MongoDB_collection: guc_cvw_20121101_20121201
# MongoDB_MUSICcollection: music_guc_cvw_20121101_20121201
# Max Number of Signals Reported: 2
# MongoDB_to_CSV_Script: /home/r01344106/code/lws_hemispheres/mongo_to_csv.py
# System Hostname: analysis1
# radar: cvw
# The "meanSubIntSpect_by_rtiCnt" is the parameter colloquially known as the SuperDARN MSTID Index.
#   It stands for the seasonal mean subtracted integrated MSTID power spectral density
#   divided by the number of range-beam-time cells that observed ground scatter.
#   It is explained in Section 2.2 of Frissell et al. (2016) (https://doi.org/10.1002/2015JA022168)
# Explanation of all parameters in data file:
#  datetime_ut: UTC time at the start of the 2-hour observation window
#  lat: Geographic latitude of center point of detection region.
#  lon: Geographic longitude of center point of detection region.
#  slt: Solar Mean Time at lat/lon point.
#  mlt: Magnetic Local Time at lat/lon point.
#  gscat: Ground scatter flag set at analysis:
#       0: all backscatter data
#       1: ground backscatter only
#       2: ionospheric backscatter only
#       3: all backscatter data with a ground backscatter flag
#  height_km: Assumed reflection point height for analysis
#  terminator_fraction: number of radar cells in daylight divided by number of radar cells in darkness.
#  good_period: True if period determined to be good for analysis. If False
#  orig_rti_cnt: Number of radar cells in window with a backscatter measurement.
#  orig_rti_fraction: orig_rti_cnt/orig_rti_possible
#  orig_rti_mean:   Mean of all measured values in the data window.
#  orig_rti_median: Median of all measured values in the data window.
#  orig_rti_possible: Total number of possible radar cells in the data window.
#  orig_rti_std: Standard deviation of all measured values in the data window.
#  intSpect: Integrated Spectrum
#            Integration of power spectral density across all radar cells and spectral bins after MSTID bandpass filter has been applied.
#  meanSubIntSpect: Radar-Season Mean Subtracted Integrated Spectrum
#                   Integration of (PSD curve of the data window minus the mean PSD curve of all data windows for this radar and season).
#  intSpect_by_rtiCnt: Integrated Spectrum normalized by the number of Range-Time-Intensity Backscatter Counts
#                      intSpect divided by orig_rti_cnt
#  meanSubIntSpect_by_rtiCnt: Radar-Season Mean Subtracted Integrated Spectrum normalized by the number of Range-Time-Intensity Backscatter Counts
#                             ** This is the MSTID Index in Frissell et al. (2016) **
#                             meanSubIntSpect divided by orig_rti_cnt
#  category_manu: Category assigned to data window in database: MSTID
#                   This is typically automatically assigned by the classification algorithm.
# reject_code Explanations:
#   0: Good Period (Not Rejected)
#   1: High Terminator Fraction (Dawn/Dusk in Observational Window
#   2: No Data
#   3: Poor Data Quality (including "Low RTI Fraction" and "Failed Quality Check")
#   4: Other (including "No RTI Fraction" and "No Terminator Fraction")
# If MUSIC Processing has been run
